    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="530"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d530">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by General <persName type="from">Hsu
                            Yung-chang</persName> to General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-10">10 June
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear General Marshall</hi>: This is to notify you that in
                    my conversation with you yesterday afternoon (9th June) you contemplated to
                    amend slightly, items (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) and (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)
                    in the proposed “Agreement to <pb facs="1034" n="1022" xml:id="pg_1022"/> Insure
                    the More Expeditious Functioning of Executive Headquarters”.<note n="48"
                        xml:id="d530fn48">May 30, <ref target="#pg_914">p. 914</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Generalissimo’s opinion is that except the words “and decisions covering the
                    local situation” in item (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) may be altered, item (<hi
                        rend="italic">a</hi>) should remain the same as you originally proposed
                    without any change.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hsu Yung Chang</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >seal</hi>)</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
